Here's how to save/restore draft text using MAUI's lifecycle events and `Preferences`:

**In your `NotePage.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
public partial class NotePage : ContentPage
{
    private const string DraftKey = "note_draft";

    public NotePage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        // Subscribe to lifecycle events
        App.Current.Windows[0].Deactivated += OnAppBackground;
        App.Current.Windows[0].Activated += OnAppForeground;
    }

    private void OnAppBackground(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, NoteEditor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    private void OnAppForeground(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(NoteEditor.Text))
        {
            NoteEditor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
        }
    }

    // Clean up when navigating away
    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        App.Current.Windows[0].Deactivated -= OnAppBackground;
        App.Current.Windows[0].Activated -= OnAppForeground;
    }

    // Clear draft after explicit save
    private void OnSaveClicked(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        // ... your save logic ...
        Preferences.Remove(DraftKey);
    }
}
```

**Alternatively, configure in `MauiProgram.cs` for global handling:**

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnStop(_ => SaveDraft())
        .OnRestart(_ => RestoreDraft()));
#elif IOS
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(_ => SaveDraft())
        .WillEnterForeground(_ => RestoreDraft()));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**
- `Deactivated`/`Activated` are cross-platform window events
- `Preferences` persists small strings across app restarts
- For large text, use `SecureStorage` or write to a file via `FileSystem.AppDataDirectory`
- Remove the draft after the user explicitly saves
